# CODEOWNERS — declare default reviewers for paths in this repo.
#
# GitHub auto-assigns the matching owner as a reviewer whenever a PR touches
# a path covered by a rule below. Replace the @placeholder owners with real
# GitHub handles or team handles when you fork this template.
#
# Syntax: <path glob> <space-separated owners>
# Patterns are evaluated bottom-to-top; the last match wins.
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-customizations/about-code-owners

# Default — every PR gets at least one reviewer.
*                                     @placeholder-owner

# User-facing documentation surface.
# Owns the Diátaxis hub, tutorials, how-to recipes, reference and explanation
# files, and the playbooks. Renames or removals here MUST update docs/README.md
# in the same PR (see CONTRIBUTING.md).
/docs/                                @placeholder-docs-owner
/docs/README.md                       @placeholder-docs-owner
/docs/tutorials/                      @placeholder-docs-owner
/docs/how-to/                         @placeholder-docs-owner

# Top-level docs that ship to readers (README, CLAUDE/AGENTS root context).
/README.md                            @placeholder-docs-owner
/CONTRIBUTING.md                      @placeholder-docs-owner

# Operational bots — own their own prompts and READMEs.
/agents/operational/                  @placeholder-ops-owner
